    <h1>CERN (European Council for Nuclear Research)</h1>
    
    <hr>
    <p>
        CERN is the world's leading laboratory for particle physics. 
        It is located on the franco-swiss border near Geneva. 
        Scientists here study the fundamental particles of the universe.
    </p>

    <br> 
    <p>
        The facility hosts the Large Hadron Collider (LHC). 
        The LHC is a 27-kilometer ring of superconducting magnets. 
        It smashes atoms together at nearly the speed of light.
    </p>

    <br> 
    <p>
        CERN is famous for proving the existence of the Higgs Boson. 
        It is also the birthplace of the World Wide Web. 
        Tim Berners-Lee invented the web here in 1989.
    </p>

